---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout
  title="shuttle secrets"
  description="Full reference for secrets subcommands: set, get, list, remove, and push."
  section="commands"
>
  <p>
    The <code>shuttle secrets</code> command group manages AES-256-GCM encrypted secrets stored
    in <code>.shuttle/secrets.enc</code>. All operations happen locally against the encrypted
    file — except <code>push</code>, which uploads secrets to the server as a <code>.env</code>
    file.
  </p>

  <h2>shuttle secrets set</h2>
  <p>Encrypt a secret and store it in the local secrets file.</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets set &lt;KEY&gt; &lt;VALUE&gt;
</code></pre>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets set DATABASE_URL "postgres://user:pass@localhost/mydb"
shuttle secrets set REDIS_URL "redis://localhost:6379"
shuttle secrets set APP_KEY "base64:..."
</code></pre>
  <p>
    If the key already exists, its value is overwritten. The secrets file is re-encrypted after
    every write.
  </p>

  <h2>shuttle secrets get</h2>
  <p>Decrypt and print the value of a single secret.</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets get &lt;KEY&gt;
</code></pre>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets get DATABASE_URL
# postgres://user:pass@localhost/mydb
</code></pre>

  <h2>shuttle secrets list</h2>
  <p>List all secret key names without revealing values.</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets list
</code></pre>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets list
# DATABASE_URL
# REDIS_URL
# APP_KEY
# MAIL_PASSWORD
</code></pre>

  <h2>shuttle secrets remove</h2>
  <p>Remove a secret from the encrypted store.</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets remove &lt;KEY&gt;
</code></pre>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets remove MAIL_PASSWORD
</code></pre>

  <h2>shuttle secrets push</h2>
  <p>
    Decrypt all secrets and upload them as a <code>.env</code> file to the server. This runs
    automatically during every <code>shuttle deploy</code>, but you can also run it manually to
    update secrets without a full deploy.
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle secrets push
</code></pre>
  <p>
    The file is written to <code>/opt/shuttle/&lt;app&gt;/&lt;app&gt;/.env</code> with mode
    <code>0600</code>. Running containers will need to be restarted to pick up the new values
    (the next deploy does this automatically).
  </p>

  <h2>Encryption details</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Algorithm</strong>: AES-256-GCM (authenticated encryption)</li>
    <li><strong>Key storage</strong>: <code>.shuttle/key</code> — 256 random bits, generated on first use</li>
    <li><strong>Ciphertext storage</strong>: <code>.shuttle/secrets.enc</code> — safe to commit</li>
    <li><strong>Integrity</strong>: GCM tag ensures tampering is detected on decrypt</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Typical workflow</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-bash"># 1. Set secrets locally
shuttle secrets set DATABASE_URL "postgres://..."
shuttle secrets set APP_SECRET "..."

# 2. Commit the encrypted file (NOT the key)
git add .shuttle/secrets.enc
git commit -m "chore: update encrypted secrets"

# 3. Deploy — secrets are pushed automatically
shuttle deploy
</code></pre>

  <h2>CI/CD workflow</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-bash"># In CI: restore the key before deploying
mkdir -p .shuttle
echo "$SHUTTLE_KEY" &gt; .shuttle/key
chmod 600 .shuttle/key

shuttle deploy   # secrets are decrypted and pushed during deploy
</code></pre>

  <h2>File protection</h2>
  <p>
    Add the key to <code>.gitignore</code> to prevent accidental commits:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">.shuttle/key
.shuttle/certs/
</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
